<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN258">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>muṭkāṟ kārai mutupaḻa ṉēyppat</l>
<l>teṟippa viḷainta tīṅkan tāra</l>
<l>niṟutta vāyan talaiceṉ ṟuṇṭu</l>
<l>paccūṉ ṟiṉṟu painniṇam perutta</l>
<l>vecci līrṅkai viṟpuṟan timirip</l>
<l>pulampuk kaṉaṉē pullaṇaṟ kāḷai</l>
<l>yorumuṟai yuṇṇā vaḷavaip perunirai</l>
<l>yūrppuṟa niṟaiyat tarukuvaṉ yārkkun</l>
<l>toṭuta lōmpumati mutukaṭ cāṭi</l>
<l>yāttarak kaḻumiya tukaḷaṉ</l>
<l>kāytalu muṇṭak kaḷvey yōṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>  Going at the head of a herd he balanced</l>
<l>against the sweet licquor fully(?) matured</l>
<l>so as to resemble the old fruits of thorny-stemmed Kārai,</l>
<l>	drinking,</l>
<l>eating fresh meat, smearing the back of [his] bow</l>
<l>with [his] hand moist with the leftovers that are thick with fresh fat</l>
<l>he entered the fields [again], the young man with a ruddy beard. </l>
<l>Before eating a single time he will bring a big heard,</l>
<l>so that the outside of the village is full, for everyone.</l>
<l>Beware of touching the old-mouthed jar </l>
<l>of him who is keen on that toddy, drinking as soon as he is thirsty,</l>
<l>he with dust that is copious as he brings the cows.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
